00:02:42.900 --> 00:02:48.290
If you're going to fold your shirts and you're
going put them away, these are the advantages:

00:02:48.290 --> 00:02:51.659
No stress on the points

00:02:51.659 --> 00:02:56.840
Speaking of, if you want your shirt to last
longer, you don't want it to hang on a hanger

00:02:56.840 --> 00:03:01.400
because eventually, hangers are going to form
indentions on your shirt.

00:03:01.400 --> 00:03:06.469
Even though cotton does kind of go back over
time, you will start to get little points

00:03:06.469 --> 00:03:07.939
there.

00:03:07.939 --> 00:03:12.079
It takes a long time for that to happen, but
it can happen.

00:03:12.079 --> 00:03:13.700
Less closet space

00:03:13.700 --> 00:03:15.459
Not all of us have walk-in closets.

00:03:15.459 --> 00:03:21.709
A lot of us have just chest drawers and we
don't have as much room to hang up our shirts,

00:03:21.709 --> 00:03:27.590
so by folding them, you take up a lot less
room in your wardrobe.

00:03:27.590 --> 00:03:28.950
Easier to pack

00:03:28.950 --> 00:03:33.540
If it's already folded, if you travel a lot
and your shirts are all folded, you could

00:03:33.540 --> 00:03:36.750
pick them and quickly put them in your suitcase.

00:03:36.750 --> 00:03:39.370
You don't have to spend time folding them

00:03:39.370 --> 00:03:43.560
Those are the big advantages of folded versus
hung.

